Here's the code for above:

    String dir1 = "/home/gordona/tmp/dir1";
    String dir2 = "/home/gordona/tmp/dir2";

    Commandline cl = new Commandline();
    cl.setWorkingDirectory(dir2);
    cl.setExecutable("cp");
    cl.createArg().setValue("-R");
    cl.createArg().setValue(dir1 + File.separator + ".");
    cl.createArg().setValue(".");
    System.out.println("command: " + cl.toString());
    try {
      cl.execute();
    } catch (CommandLineException ex) {
      ex.printStackTrace();
    }

Note that you *need* to have the last '.' in a separate createArg() call or Commandline will lumb them all together in the same set of tick marks and "cp" will complain about missing the destination file operand.
